rComments: One of the worst lecturers ever. She never seemed to understand what she was talking about, and always acted confused? Was she stoned? I mean seriously, she makes about 10 factual errors per lecture, and if anyone speaks up, she blubbers and sputters and can't clarify because she is perpetually confused. She can't lecture. Easy A though.

Awful class! Lectures whole time...for the first exam i had over 26 pages of TYPED notes!! Final is cumulative(over 75 pages of typed notes)! Must go to class for pop quizes...not just if you are there you get points...they are incredible hard. No curve of tests! just a simply awful teacaher and class that excepts WAY WAY to much out of non-majors!

Class is a bit boring, there are few things that are interesting here and there. She lectures the whole time. She doesn't post any of her notes. She also gives out pop quizes to make sure to be there. Overall, okay class for a gen ed but not very interesting.
